## 5. USING THE APP
[cite_start]The system features two primary functional requirements:

### 5.1 Predicting Rainfall From A Dataset
[cite_start]Implemented on the app's homepage, this module is utilized to conduct research on rainfall prediction to find the lowest MAPE value using genetic algorithm parameters: generation size, population size, crossover rate, and mutation rate. 

> [cite_start]**Caution:** The values that can be input for crossover rate and mutation rate are limited to a range between 0 and 1! [cite_start]If they are outside of this range, the program will display an error message. [cite_start]Additionally, each parameter only accepts numerical input data.

### 5.2 Predicting Rainfall From New Data
[cite_start]Implemented on the *Manual Forecasting* page, this module is used to predict rainfall values from new data. [cite_start]The boundaries of the fuzzy membership functions used are taken from the chromosome that produced the best fitness score during the research. [cite_start]Users can input attribute values for temperature, air humidity, air pressure, and wind speed to generate a forecast.

## 6. CLASS IMPLEMENTATION

* [cite_start]**`GeneticAlgorithm.java`**: This abstract superclass is utilized to receive input data from the `Main.java` class and initiates the process of searching for a chromosome that can generate membership function boundaries with the best fitness value. [cite_start]The stage starts from initializing the initial population to computing the fitness value.
* [cite_start]**`FISTsukamoto.java`**: A subclass of `GeneticAlgorithm.java` used to calculate the rainfall value using the Tsukamoto FIS method. [cite_start]This class also computes the Absolute Percentage Error (APE) and Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE), returning the MAPE values to the superclass. [cite_start]The process encompasses fuzzification, rule-based implication, and defuzzification.
* [cite_start]**`Main.java`**: Represents the application's GUI, comprising the Homepage and the Manual Forecasting page.

